-- England Picks Flood for Second Rugby Test Against South Africa
-- B y
-- 2012-06-14T10:18:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-14/england-picks-flood-for-second-rugby-test-against-south-africa.html
England coach Stuart Lancaster
picked  Toby Flood  ahead of Owen Farrell at fly-half for the
second rugby Test against South Africa in Johannesburg on June
16.  England lost the first match 22-17 in Durban on June 9. The
third and final Test is in  Port Elizabeth  on June 23.  England team:
B. Foden (Northampton); C. Ashton (Northampton), J. Joseph
(London Irish), M. Tuilagi (Leicester), D. Strettle (Saracens);
T. Flood (Leicester), B. Youngs (Leicester); J. Marler
(Harlequins), D. Hartley (Northampton), D. Cole (Leicester), M.
Botha (Saracens), G. Parling (Leicester), T. Johnson (Exeter),
C. Robshaw (Harlequins, capt.), B. Morgan (Scarlets).  Replacements: L. Mears (Bath), A. Corbisiero (London Irish),
T. Palmer (Stade Francais), P. Dowson (Northampton), L. Dickson
(Northampton), O. Farrell (Saracens), A. Goode (Saracens).  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
